  "text": "The quantitative semantics returns a real value that can be interpreted as a measure of the strength with which the specification is satisfied or falsified by an observed trajectory. More specifically, the sign of such a satisfaction score is related to the truth of the formula (positive stands for true), while the absolute value of the score is a measure of the robustness of the satisfaction or dissatisfaction. This definition of quantitative measure is based on [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and it is a reformulation of the robustness degree of [CITATION_3] .",
